HEADWORD: kickoff
<hw>kickoff</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Football)</fld> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
kick from the center of the field to start a football game or to resume
it after a score.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the time at which an event or activity
begins.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> beginning, commencement, first, outset, start,
starting time, offset.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>kick off</ent>⟦br⟧
